{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/bash/11-positional-parameters/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Rahul's Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a2c9d9c9-4d52-5f86-a7dd-1732fe570bb9","excerpt":"","html":"<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token shebang important\">#!/bin/bash</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># positional parameters are variables that can store data on the command line in variable names 0-9</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># $0 always contains the path tp the executed script</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># you can access names past 9 by using parameter expansio like this ${10}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># add all numbers on the command line</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"1st argument: <span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">sum</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># $# tells you the number of arguments</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$#</span> -gt <span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># get the first argument</span>\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">num</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">sum</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$((</span>sum<span class=\"token operator\">+</span>num<span class=\"token variable\">))</span></span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># shift moves the value of $2 into $1 until none are left</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># the value of $# decrements as well</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">shift</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">done</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Sum: <span class=\"token variable\">$sum</span>\"</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Positional Parameters","date":"July 21, 2020","description":"learn how access, and use positional parameters in bash shell scripting"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/bash/11-positional-parameters/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/bash/4-integer-test/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Logical Operators and integer conditional statements"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/bash/12-value-seperator/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Value seperator in strings"}}}}}